                Dr. Naser P. Sharifi received his B.Sc. degree in 2009, and his M.Sc. degree in 2011. He also received his Ph.D. degree from the Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering at Worcester Polytechnic Institute, MA, USA in 2016. Dr. Sharifi’s research interests include sustainability of infrastructure, novel construction and pavement materials, and concrete technology. He has worked on research projects supported by Federal Highway Administration, Pennsylvania Department of Transportation (DOT), Michigan DOT, and Pitt IRISE. Dr. Sharifi has over 22 publications in archival journals and conference proceedings. He has served as the revision committee member for ASTM D7369-11, and the reviewer in several journals such as Construction and Building Materials, Cement and Concrete Composites, and Journal of Advances in Civil Engineering Materials. Dr. Sharifi is a registered Professional Engineer (PE - Civil Structural)

